'''to lose one's rag''' (''past tense and past participle'' '''lost one's rag''')

#(''colloquial'') To become [[angry]].

====Usage note====
*Used with '''with''' when the anger directed at a person <!-- or "at", or something else? -->
*:''When I told him about the accident, he lost his rang with me.''
*Used with '''about''' or '''over''' when the anger is caused by an event
*:''There's no need to lose your rag over missing the train!''

